  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table width=85% border=0 cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0 align=center>
  <tr>
    <td bgcolor='0e024d' class='spti2'>THE DISCIPLINE OF INNERFLAME</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Class:</b>&nbsp;Monk</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Level obtained:</b>&nbsp;56</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Duration:</b>&nbsp;12 seconds.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay:</b>&nbsp;30 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay at Level 60:</b>&nbsp;26 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b><u>Discipline Description:</u></b><P>When using this discipline all hits landed by the monk will be for at least four times the base weapons/hand damage. For example: If you used a weapon with a base damage of 8, then you would receive a bonus of 32 damage on every hit for the duration of the discipline.  This discipline lasts for 12 seconds and has a base reuse time of 30 minutes.  The reuse time for this discipline will decrease as the monk gains additional levels.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>  <table border='0' width='100%' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5'>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='#000066' class='spti2'>DISCIPLINE COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>SOMETHINGS WRONG W/ YOUR MATH</span><b>, By Trasnt</b> <small>(6/27/2001)</small><br><br>Im 56 and the high dmg i do with a tranquil staff and this disc is 133, TK's seem to be about 116 *shrug*<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>THIS IS HOW IT WORKS</span><b>, By Dragaicn</b> <small>(5/24/2001)</small><br><br>Ok, say you have a Tranquil staff 29dmg 30dly...when using this discipline you will hit for <i>at least</i> 116dmg (29 X 4). with T staff. I can hit for close to 150 unbuffed at lvl 53 but I can also hit for like 50dmg, 10dmg, etc., so all this does is every hit that you 'land' will do a minium of the dmg on the weapon which in this case would be 116dmg...so you will be hitting for 116dmg+ <i>every hit you land</i>.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>OH MY...</span><b>, By Syui chan</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>Could you imagine this discipline with a Ton Po's Bo Stick of Understanding? 44x4 = 176.  Wow!

<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>YOU GUYS ARE CONFUSED</span><b>, By Smagh</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>In the description it says that it does 4 times the damage of your weapon/hand ADDED on to your normal hits. The reason they word it like that is because they want you to know the formula they use just so you are in the know. Most damages at higher levels do 4 the damage of the damage it says on the weapons. This discipline does an additional 4 times added on just like the first 4 is added on. For example with 12 damage weapons you usually do about 50 damage without this discipline, with this it'd add an additional 4 times the damage of the weapon's damage stats so an additional 50 damage. In other words it's usually going to double each hit you do. This is still remarkable but it's not quite 4 times your normal damage like you guys were saying.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>EXAMPLE</span><b>, By Zerric</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>Ok I use a Runed fighters staff ( 19 / 20 ).I can hit unbuffed for 93 dmg. Max
With this weapon and using the 56th level disc my dmg would look like this. Zerric hits Mobx for 93 +(4 x 19) = 169,Zerric hits Mobx for 93 +(4 x 19) = 169,Zerric hits Mobx for 93 +(4 x 19) = 169,Zerric Kicks Mobx for 110 +(4 x 25) = 210.<P>
Therefore it does 4 times the BASE DMG of the weap. In my case 19. 19 x 4 = 76.. add this to my 93. Boom. 169



<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
